/-- Absolute control for the actual rough-count Euler-product discrepancy in
the modulus-one lane.  The theorem below proves that this is exactly the same
content as the signed-multiples carrier bound. -/
def roughDyadicRoughWindowEulerProductDiscrepancyAbsBoundModulusOne
    (a₀ b₀ _C₀ E X₀ : ℝ) : Prop :=
  0 ≤ E ∧ ∀ X : ℝ, X₀ ≤ X →
    ∀ t : ℝ, X ^ a₀ ≤ t → t ≤ 2 * X ^ b₀ →
      |roughDyadicRoughWindowCount X t -
        t * roughDyadicBadPrimeMainEulerProduct X| ≤
        E * (t / Real.log (EscAnalytic.zScale X))

/-- Normalized absolute control for the actual rough-count Euler-product
discrepancy in the modulus-one lane.  This is the familiar relative-error form:
after dividing by the sieve scale `t/log z`, the discrepancy is at most `E`.
