/-- The normalized positive-range explicit floor-error target directly
discharges the signed-multiples primitive consumed by the live public route.
All conversions in this bridge are finite floor/count bookkeeping; the only
remaining analytic content is the smallness of the normalized alternating
floor-error sum itself. -/
theorem LinearSieveRoughDyadicMultiplesSignedErrorQuarterBoundOnPositiveRanges_of_floorErrorNormalized
    (h : RoughDyadicFloorErrorUniformNormalizedSmallBoundOnPositiveRanges) :
